headline: Putin lets Armenian fund buy Goldman Sachs stakes in Russian public companies
summary: Russian President Vladimir Putin has authorised Armenian investment fund Balchug Capital to buy shares owned by Goldman Sachs' Russian subsidiary in nine major companies, mostly in Russia's energy sector, according to a decree published on Wednesday. Balchug Capital and Goldman Sachs did not immediately respond to requests for comment. Balchug Capital was given the green light to purchase Goldman Sachs' subsidiary in Russia in January, according to a separate decree, paving the way for the U.S. bank to withdraw from the Russian market and extract some capital stranded there.
